Intervention: There are no arms or subgroups in this study.
Eligibility: This study will include a population of women aged 25 years and older who require a breast MRI examination at MAYO CLINIC ROCHESTER.
Patients should not be breast-feeding or pregnant.
All women of childbearing potential should have had a negative pregnancy test within 2 days of the MBI study.
Women who are scheduled for a breast MRI examination for clinical concern, problem solving or further assessment of invasive breast cancer (e.g., pre-operative establishment of known breast cancer).
They are unable to understand and sign the consent form
They are physically unable to sit upright and still for 40 minutes.
The mammary MRI is used for screening purposes or to determine the state of breast augmentation.
They had breast surgery in the previous year.
Results: Sensitivity is the number of women with breast cancer detected by many women with breast cancer diagnosed by surgery or biopsy.
Time: within 1 week of surgery or biopsy
Title of the arm/group: Participants in the study
Description of the arm/group: There are no arms or subgroups in this study.
Unit of measure: participants MBI sensitivity: 25
